# .gitignore
#
# WHY THIS FILE IS CRITICAL:
# Everything listed here is NEVER committed to GitHub.
# The most important line is .env — your secrets file.
# One accidental git push with .env = all your API keys exposed.
# Automated bots scan GitHub for leaked credentials within seconds.

# ─── SECRETS (MOST CRITICAL) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env.staging
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
secrets/
# WHY: these files contain real API keys, database passwords, JWT secrets.
# Exposing them = your database wiped, your API quotas drained, your
# accounts compromised. This line protects everything.

# ─── PYTHON ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
# WHY: compiled Python files — regenerated automatically, no value in git

# Virtual environment
venv/
env/
.venv/
ENV/
# WHY: your virtual environment is specific to your machine.
# Other developers install their own with: pip install -r requirements.txt

# Distribution / packaging
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
*.egg

# ─── TESTING & COVERAGE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
coverage.xml
*.cover
# WHY: test artifacts — regenerated by running tests

# ─── AI MODELS (LARGE FILES) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.pt
*.pth
*.bin
*.gguf
models/
whisper_models/
tts_models/
# WHY: AI model weights are gigabytes in size.
# GitHub has a 100MB file limit.
# Models are downloaded at startup or kept on the server.

# ─── DATABASE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
# WHY: local SQLite files (used in testing) should not go to GitHub.
# Production uses PostgreSQL — SQLite is dev/test only.

# ─── LOGS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
logs/
*.log
# WHY: logs can contain sensitive information.
# Also they're large and change constantly — bad for git history.

# ─── GENERATED FILES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/tmp/
reports/
*.pdf
# WHY: generated PDF reports are user data, not code.

# ─── CHROMADB LOCAL DATA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
chroma_data/
.chroma/
# WHY: local ChromaDB data is large and machine-specific.
# The drug knowledge base is loaded from scripts at setup time.

# ─── IDE & EDITOR ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/settings.json
# WHY: settings.json can contain personal paths and preferences.
# We DO commit .vscode/extensions.json (recommended extensions for the team).
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
# WHY: macOS metadata files — irrelevant to other developers

# ─── DOCKER ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# We DO commit Dockerfile and docker-compose.yml
# We do NOT commit local Docker volumes or build cache
.docker/

# ─── NODE (FRONTEND) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
frontend/dist/
frontend/build/
.npm

# ─── MISC ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.bak
*.tmp
.cache/